Articles.Content:
Full purge of both KSP and Unity3d files. Purge of savegame. Verified issue in 100% stock 1.2 (Screenshot has a mod part in it).
This has been a graphics bug since a late September prerelease build. It happens on Minmus and Pol, possibly others, but only planet surface textures.

Tried --force-glcore, changed anti-aliasing and texture quality with no effect.

Running Linux / AMD-radeon.
Anybody else have this problem?

Hi @ExtremeSquared, needless to say KSP should not look like that, but without more info it's extremely hard to figure out what's going on, so please see this thread.

We'll need your logs from KSP, your hardware info including OS version and gpu driver versions.

Also how hot is your PC getting and how old is it?

Most likely not a hardware issue. 1.1.3 works fine, and most "biomes" work fine too.

I saw nothing interesting in the logs, but I'll post them tomorrow. I believe the AMD/radeon module was the r600 driver, but I can double check that too.

I'm used to various Unity graphics incompatibilities popping up at this point, but they are usually widely reported and quickly sidestepped.

This is more than likely a driver issue. Update/revert and report back.

Edited October 28, 2016 by Majorjim!

Driver is up to date / refreshed. My shot-in-the-dark guess is that, as usual, bleeding edge Unity has compatibility regressions. Is KSP on U5.7 right now?

This log file is from doing nothing but loading a clean save on a clean install, then navigating to a vessel landed on a texture-glitched surface.
